## Process Management (Windows PowerShell)

### Kill All Node.js Processes
```powershell
Get-Process node -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force
```

### Check What's Using a Port
```powershell
netstat -ano | findstr ":3000"
```

### Kill Process by PID
```powershell
taskkill /PID <pid> /F
```

### List All Node Processes with Details
```powershell
Get-Process node -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Id, ProcessName, StartTime, @{Name='Memory(MB)';Expression={[math]::Round($_.WorkingSet64/1MB,2)}}
```

### Find Process by Port and Kill It
```powershell
# Find PID on port 3000
$pid = (netstat -ano | findstr ":3000" | findstr "LISTENING")[0] -replace '.*\s+(\d+)$','$1'
taskkill /PID $pid /F
```

